Quetion:3.  Create a navigation bar similar to question 1. For each navigation item, use a different border style.
Answer: 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Navigation bar</title>
    <style>
        nav{
            background-color: aqua;
            padding:20px;
        }
        a {
            color: #fff;
            margin-right: 20px;
            margin-left: 20px; 
        }
        a:hover {
            color: #000;
        }
        .nav-link-1 {
            border: 3px solid black;
            padding: 5px;
        }
        .nav-link-2  {
            border: 3px dotted black;
            padding: 5px;

        }
        .nav-link-3 {
            border: 3px solid olive;
            padding: 5px;
        }
        .nav-link-4 {
            border: 3px dotted green;
            padding: 5px; 
               }
               .nav-link-5 {
                border: 3px solid black ;
                padding: 5px;
               }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link-1">Home</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link-2">About Us</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link-3">Contact</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link-4">Blog</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link-5">Login</a>
        </nav>
</body>
</html>

Question:4.Create a simple webpage with an image and make the image circlar using border-radius.
Answer.
  <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>image border</title>
    <style>
        img{
            background-color: red;
            border-radius: 100px ;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
   <img src="https://starsunfolded.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Alakh-Pandey.jpg" alt="alakh sir">
   </body>
   </html>

