Question:7. Create a simple webpage with a card similar to question nmber 2. The card must be semi-transparent as default and on hovering the card must be displaed clearly. Use CSS apacity to achieve this output.
Answer:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>card</title>
    <style>.courseImage {
height: 200px;
width: 300px;
border-radius: 20px;
}
div {
margin: 0 auto;
background-color: #f8c42e;
width: 300px;
padding: 10px;
border-radius: 20px;
opacity: 0.5;
}
div:hover {
opacity: 1;
}

</style>
</head>
<body> 
    
    <div>
<img class="courseImage" src="https://cdn.pwskills.com/assets/uploads/
thumbnails/64215310af09d6aa495682f5.jpg"
alt=" PW SKills web development" />
<p><b>Course Name:</b> PW SKills web development</p>
</div>
    
</body>
</html>

Question:8.  Create  simple list of item as mentioned below.
solution.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>list of style</title>
    <style> 
        li{
            list-style-type: lower lower-roman;
        }
        </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Requirements</h1>
<ul>
<li>System with minimum i3 processor or better.</li>
<li>At least 4 GB of RAM.</li>
<li>Working internet connection.</li>
<li>Dedication to learn</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>
